# Architecture: {{ display_name }}

## Overview

**{{ display_name }}** is a Next.js {{ nextjs_version }} frontend application using the **{{ router }}** with **{{ styling }}** for styling and **{{ state_management }}** for client state.

## Principles

1. **Server first**: Push as much logic as possible to the server. Reach for Server Components before Client Components.
2. **Separation of concerns**: UI rendering, data fetching, and business logic live in distinct layers.
3. **Colocation**: Keep files close to where they are used. Feature code lives in `src/components/features/`.
4. **Typed contracts**: All API responses and component props are typed. No `any`.
5. **Explicit loading and error states**: Every data-fetching boundary has a loading skeleton and error fallback.

---

## Routing Structure

{% if router == "app-router" %}
### App Router (Next.js {{ nextjs_version }})

The App Router uses the file system under `src/app/`. Each folder is a route segment. Special files (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`) map to React concepts.

```
src/app/
├── layout.tsx              # Root layout - fonts, global providers, metadata
├── page.tsx                # "/" home page
├── loading.tsx             # Root-level Suspense fallback
├── error.tsx               # Root-level error boundary
├── not-found.tsx           # 404 page
│
├── (auth)/                 # Route group: no shared layout with dashboard
│   ├── login/
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   └── register/
│       └── page.tsx
│
├── (dashboard)/            # Route group: shared authenticated layout
│   ├── layout.tsx          # Sidebar + header shell
│   ├── dashboard/
│   │   ├── page.tsx        # Server Component - fetches data at request time
│   │   └── loading.tsx     # Skeleton while data loads
│   ├── [entity]/
│   │   ├── page.tsx        # List page
│   │   └── [id]/
│   │       └── page.tsx    # Detail page
│   └── settings/
│       └── page.tsx
│
└── api/                    # API route handlers (BFF pattern)
    └── [resource]/
        └── route.ts        # GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE handlers
```

**Route Groups** (`(auth)`, `(dashboard)`) organise routes without affecting the URL. Use them to scope layouts.

{% else %}
### Pages Router (Next.js {{ nextjs_version }})

The Pages Router lives under `src/pages/`. Each file maps directly to a URL.

```
src/pages/
├── _app.tsx                # Global providers, layout wrapper, global styles
├── _document.tsx           # HTML document customisation (fonts, meta)
├── index.tsx               # "/" home page
├── 404.tsx                 # Not found page
├── 500.tsx                 # Error page
│
├── auth/
│   ├── login.tsx
│   └── register.tsx
│
├── dashboard/
│   └── index.tsx           # /dashboard
│
├── [entity]/
│   ├── index.tsx           # /[entity] list page
│   └── [id].tsx            # /[entity]/[id] detail page
│
└── api/                    # API routes
    └── [resource]/
        └── index.ts
```

Data fetching uses `getServerSideProps` (per-request) or `getStaticProps` (build-time / ISR).

{% endif %}

