## Data Fetching Patterns

{% if router == "app-router" %}
### Server Components (default)

Use Server Components for any data that can be fetched at request time without client interactivity.

```tsx
// src/app/(dashboard)/users/page.tsx
// No "use client" directive = Server Component
import { UserTable } from "@/components/features/UserTable";
import { getUsers } from "@/services/users";

export default async function UsersPage() {
  const users = await getUsers(); // direct async call, no useEffect
  return <UserTable users={users} />;
}
```

Advantages:
- Zero client-side JavaScript for the data fetch
- Data is never exposed in the network tab
- Automatic deduplication with `fetch` cache

### Client Components

Add `"use client"` only when you need:
- Browser APIs (`window`, `localStorage`, `navigator`)
- React hooks that require client state (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useReducer`)
- Event handlers that need immediate interactivity
- Third-party libraries that are not server-compatible

```tsx
"use client";
// src/components/features/SearchBar.tsx
import { useState } from "react";

export function SearchBar({ onSearch }: { onSearch: (q: string) => void }) {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState("");
  // ...
}
```

### Suspense Boundaries

Wrap async Server Components in `<Suspense>` to stream content progressively.

```tsx
import { Suspense } from "react";
import { UserTableSkeleton } from "@/components/ui/UserTableSkeleton";

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <main>
      <h1>Users</h1>
      <Suspense fallback={<UserTableSkeleton />}>
        <UserTable /> {/* async server component */}
      </Suspense>
    </main>
  );
}
```

### `loading.tsx` vs `<Suspense>`

- `loading.tsx`: automatic Suspense boundary for the entire page segment
- `<Suspense>`: fine-grained control within a page - prefer this for partial loading

{% else %}
### Pages Router Data Fetching

| Method | When to use |
|--------|-------------|
| `getServerSideProps` | Data changes per request (user-specific, real-time) |
| `getStaticProps` | Data can be pre-built (marketing pages, public content) |
| `getStaticPaths` + `getStaticProps` | Dynamic routes with known IDs at build time |
| Client-side (`useEffect` / React Query) | Data that changes after interaction (search, filters) |

```tsx
// src/pages/users/index.tsx
import type { GetServerSideProps } from "next";

export const getServerSideProps: GetServerSideProps = async (ctx) => {
  const users = await getUsers();
  return { props: { users } };
};
```

{% endif %}

