## State Management

{% if state_management == "zustand" %}
### Zustand

Client-only UI state (modals, sidebar open/closed, user preferences) lives in Zustand stores. Server state (API data) belongs in TanStack Query or Server Components - not in Zustand.

```
src/lib/stores/
├── ui.store.ts       # sidebar, modals, toasts
├── auth.store.ts     # current user session (if custom-jwt)
└── index.ts
```

**Store pattern:**

```ts
// src/lib/stores/ui.store.ts
import { create } from "zustand";
import { persist } from "zustand/middleware";

interface UIState {
  sidebarOpen: boolean;
  toggleSidebar: () => void;
}

export const useUIStore = create<UIState>()(
  persist(
    (set) => ({
      sidebarOpen: true,
      toggleSidebar: () => set((s) => ({ sidebarOpen: !s.sidebarOpen })),
    }),
    { name: "ui-preferences" }
  )
);
```

{% elif state_management == "jotai" %}
### Jotai

Atomic state management. Each atom represents a single unit of state. Compose atoms to derive computed state.

```
src/lib/atoms/
├── ui.atoms.ts       # sidebar, modal, toast atoms
├── auth.atoms.ts     # session atoms
└── index.ts
```

```ts
// src/lib/atoms/ui.atoms.ts
import { atom } from "jotai";
import { atomWithStorage } from "jotai/utils";

export const sidebarOpenAtom = atomWithStorage("sidebarOpen", true);
export const activeModalAtom = atom<string | null>(null);
```

{% elif state_management == "redux-toolkit" %}
### Redux Toolkit

State is split into slices. Each feature owns its slice. Use `createAsyncThunk` only when needed - prefer TanStack Query for server state.

```
src/lib/store/
├── index.ts          # configureStore
├── hooks.ts          # typed useAppSelector, useAppDispatch
└── slices/
    ├── ui.slice.ts
    └── auth.slice.ts
```

{% elif state_management == "react-query-only" %}
### TanStack Query Only (No Client Store)

Server state is in TanStack Query. Ephemeral UI state (open dialogs, form dirty state) is local `useState`. No global client store.

This is intentionally minimal. Introduce a store only if you find yourself passing UI state through more than 2 component layers.

{% endif %}

