{% if use_auth %}
## Authentication

{% if auth_provider == "next-auth" %}
### NextAuth.js

Auth is handled by NextAuth.js (Auth.js v5 in Next.js 15). Configuration lives in `src/lib/auth.ts`.

```
src/lib/auth.ts         # NextAuth config: providers, callbacks, session
src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts   # Auth API route
src/middleware.ts        # Route protection via NextAuth middleware
```

**Protecting routes** - `src/middleware.ts`:

```ts
export { auth as middleware } from "@/lib/auth";

export const config = {
  matcher: ["/(dashboard)/:path*", "/api/:path*"],
};
```

**Session in Server Components:**

```ts
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth";

export default async function Page() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session) redirect("/login");
  return <Dashboard user={session.user} />;
}
```

{% elif auth_provider == "clerk" %}
### Clerk

Clerk handles all auth UI, sessions, and token management. No custom auth code required.

```
src/middleware.ts    # clerkMiddleware() - protects routes
src/lib/clerk.ts    # Clerk client config
```

**Protecting routes:**

```ts
// src/middleware.ts
import { clerkMiddleware, createRouteMatcher } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const isProtected = createRouteMatcher(["/(dashboard)(.*)"]);

export default clerkMiddleware((auth, req) => {
  if (isProtected(req)) auth().protect();
});
```

{% elif auth_provider == "custom-jwt" %}
### Custom JWT

Tokens are stored in `HttpOnly` cookies (not `localStorage`). The JWT is validated in middleware on every request to a protected route.

```
src/lib/auth/
├── jwt.ts          # sign, verify, decode helpers
├── cookies.ts      # getToken, setToken, clearToken
└── middleware.ts   # route protection logic
src/middleware.ts   # Next.js middleware entry
```

**Never store JWTs in localStorage** - `HttpOnly` cookies are not accessible to JavaScript, preventing XSS token theft.

{% endif %}
{% endif %}

