## Styling Architecture

{% if styling == "tailwind" %}
### Tailwind CSS

Design tokens are defined in `tailwind.config.ts`. Custom colours, fonts, and spacing extend the base theme.

```
src/styles/
├── globals.css          # @tailwind directives, CSS custom properties
└── typography.css       # Prose styles (optional)
```

**Conventions:**
- Use semantic colour names (`text-foreground`, `bg-card`) from the design token layer, not raw values (`text-gray-900`).
- Complex component styles use `cva` (class-variance-authority) to manage variants.
- Never use `@apply` in component files - use Tailwind classes in JSX directly.

```tsx
// Use cva for variant-based components
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const button = cva("inline-flex items-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors", {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      primary: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
      ghost: "hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground",
    },
    size: {
      sm: "h-8 px-3 text-sm",
      md: "h-10 px-4",
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: "primary", size: "md" },
});
```

{% elif styling == "css-modules" %}
### CSS Modules

Each component has a colocated `.module.css` file. Global styles and tokens are in `src/styles/`.

```
src/styles/
├── globals.css         # CSS custom properties (design tokens), resets
├── tokens.css          # --color-*, --spacing-*, --font-* variables
└── typography.css      # Base typography rules
```

**Convention:** Component styles are in `ComponentName.module.css` next to `ComponentName.tsx`. Never use global class names in component files.

{% elif styling == "styled-components" %}
### Styled Components

Theme tokens are defined in `src/styles/theme.ts` and provided via `ThemeProvider`. Use `styled` for component styles and `css` helper for reusable style fragments.

```
src/styles/
├── theme.ts            # DefaultTheme: colors, spacing, typography
├── GlobalStyles.ts     # createGlobalStyle - resets and base styles
└── mixins.ts           # Reusable css`` fragments
```

**SSR:** Styled Components requires the `ServerStyleSheet` pattern for correct server-side rendering in Next.js.

{% elif styling == "scss" %}
### SCSS

Styles use SCSS with a 7-1 partial architecture. Variables and mixins are defined in `src/styles/abstracts/`.

```
src/styles/
├── abstracts/
│   ├── _variables.scss   # Design tokens as SCSS variables
│   ├── _mixins.scss      # Responsive breakpoints, flex helpers
│   └── _functions.scss
├── base/
│   ├── _reset.scss
│   └── _typography.scss
├── components/           # Global component overrides (avoid - prefer colocated)
└── main.scss             # Imports all partials
```

Component-level SCSS uses colocated `.module.scss` files to avoid global scope pollution.

{% endif %}

