{% if ui_library == "shadcn-ui" %}
## UI Components: shadcn/ui

Components are copied into `src/components/ui/` via the `shadcn` CLI. They are yours to modify.

```bash
# Add a new component
pnpx shadcn@latest add button
pnpx shadcn@latest add dialog
```

Components sit in `src/components/ui/`. **Do not import directly from the shadcn registry** - always use the local copy so customisation is possible.

{% elif ui_library == "radix-ui" %}
## UI Components: Radix UI

Radix UI provides unstyled, accessible primitives. Compose them in `src/components/ui/` and apply styling with {{ styling }}.

```tsx
// src/components/ui/Dialog.tsx
import * as RadixDialog from "@radix-ui/react-dialog";

export const Dialog = RadixDialog.Root;
export const DialogTrigger = RadixDialog.Trigger;
export const DialogContent = /* styled wrapper */ ...;
```

{% elif ui_library == "headless-ui" %}
## UI Components: Headless UI

Headless UI components are framework-integrated (React). Wrap them in `src/components/ui/` to add consistent styling.

{% endif %}

