## Performance Patterns

### Image Optimisation

Always use `next/image` instead of `<img>`. Provide explicit `width` and `height` (or `fill` with a positioned parent) to prevent layout shift (CLS).

```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

<Image
  src="/hero.webp"
  alt="..."
  width={800}
  height={450}
  priority // above the fold only
/>
```

### Dynamic Imports

Use `next/dynamic` for components that are large, client-only, or not needed on initial render.

```tsx
import dynamic from "next/dynamic";

const HeavyChart = dynamic(() => import("@/components/features/HeavyChart"), {
  loading: () => <ChartSkeleton />,
  ssr: false, // charts often require window
});
```

### Font Loading

Use `next/font` to self-host fonts and eliminate layout shift from Google Fonts.

```ts
// src/app/layout.tsx
import { Inter } from "next/font/google";

const inter = Inter({ subsets: ["latin"], variable: "--font-sans" });
```

### Metadata

Every page exports a `metadata` object (App Router) or `<Head>` content (Pages Router) for SEO.

```ts
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: `${entity.name} | {{ display_name }}`,
  description: entity.description,
};
```

